title: ICE: inherent_associated_types: `Unexpected parameter Type(..) ...  when substituting in region..`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(inherent_associated_types)] pub struct Carrier<'a>(&'a ()); pub type User = for<'b> fn(Carrier<'b>::Focus); impl<'a> Carrier<'a> { pub type Focus = &'a mut User; } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.71.0-nightly (8b4b20836 2023-05-22) binary: rustc commit-hash: 8b4b20836b832e91aa605a2faf5e2a55190202c8 commit-date: 2023-05-22 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.71.0-nightly LLVM version: 16.0.4 ``` ### Error output ``` ```
